\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26 The Christmas Eve party buzzed with merriment, laughter and festive music spilling out into the hallway. Evan lingered by the door, sharing a warm goodbye with Laura. His forced smile faltered, a flicker of unease clouding his features. Regret tugged at him; Maggie had invited him to stay the night, and he }{\f2\fs28\b0\i1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>refused<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26  under the guise of spending Christmas morning with his mother and Liz. The excuse held a grain of truth, but guilt settled over him like an unwelcome guest. He pushed the unsettling feelings aside for now, focusing on the moment.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26 "It's been a wonderful night, Maggie," Evan said, his eyes meeting hers. "I wish I could stay."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26 Maggie's face fell slightly. "I know," she replied, a trace of disappointment in her tone. "It's okay. Christmas is family time."}
